bilingual.target: 这份报告包含了有价值的数据。

bilingual.source: His advice is deemed to be valuable.
bilingual.target: 他的建议被认为是有价值的。

bilingual.source: A CPA can provide valuable tax advice.
bilingual.target: 注册会计师可以提供有价值的税务建议。

bilingual.source: The house is the most valuable asset they own.
bilingual.target: 这栋房子是他们拥有的最有价值的资产。
经纪人提供了有价值的市场见解。

bilingual.source: He earns his vig by providing valuable advice.
bilingual.target: 他通过提供有价值的建议来赚取佣金。

bilingual.source: Miners extract valuable minerals from the earth.
bilingual.target: 矿工从地下提取有价值的矿物。

bilingual.source: This book provides a lot of valuable edification.
bilingual.target: 这本书提供了很多有价值的教诲。

bilingual.source: She provided valuable insights during the meeting.
bilingual.target: 她在会议中提供了有价值的见解。

bilingual.source: The scout reported back with valuable intelligence.
bilingual.target: 侦察员带回了有价值的情报。

list.abstract: 《Valuable》是美国另类摇滚乐队Remedy Drive演唱的歌曲，收录于2008年8月26日发行的专辑《Daylight Is Coming》。

yingyinNormal.en: But it turns out that manure is a valuable source of power, thanks to its natural byproduct, methane gas.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但由于原料的天然副产品-沼气，它却成了有价值的能源。

yingyinNormal.en: Assistant Director Green and I will bring whatever is valuable forward. I want direct access. Live streaming.
yingyinNormal.zh: 格林副处长和我会汇报任何有价值的情报。我想要直接访问权。实时影像。

yingyinNormal.en: I will not. Parties are useless and take up valuable Boov time.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我不去，派对毫无益处，还浪费宝贵的波波时间。

yingyinNormal.en: Think of it as us saying, "You're just too valuable to promote."
yingyinNormal.zh: 这样想"太有才了，舍不得让升职"。

yingyinNormal.en: You know how valuable that is now? You know what that makes you?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你知道现在有多重要吗? 知道这种技能会让你变成什么吗?

yingyinNormal.en: It was the tin itself that was valuable, what you could do with it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 而是罐子本身它的价值还有用途。

yingyinNormal.en: The board will do nothing. Our arrangement is too valuable to them.
yingyinNormal.zh: 董事会什么都不会做的，我们的协议对他们而言太过重要。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, she is. She's terrific. And she's proving to be a valuable roommate.
yingyinNormal.zh: 没错，她太棒了，真的是一位好室友。

yingyinNormal.en: My letter of resignation. I can't accept that. You're too valuable to us.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我的辞呈。我不能接受，你对我们太重要了。

yingyinNormal.en: You get my people, you have a clear win in both states. My endorsement is valuable.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你得到我选民的支持，就能在两个州稳赢。我的支持是很宝贵的。

yingyinNormal.en: Not a thinker. Not a leader. Simply a face plucked for the masses. Was she valuable?
yingyinNormal.zh: 既不是是思想家，也没成为领袖，只是被民众硬推到了前台，她的存在是否有意义呢？

yingyinNormal.en: Penny, this would be a massive undertaking, and my time is both limited and valuable.
yingyinNormal.zh: 佩妮，教你可是艰巨的任务，我的时间既有限又宝贵呢。

yingyinNormal.en: Because you get to keep something, because it's very valuable, which is social relationships.
yingyinNormal.zh: 因为你要保持住，因为它很珍贵，这就是社会关系。

yingyinNormal.en: She was extremely valuable to you rebellion. Because you have no vision, no true leader among you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 对反叛军来说当然很有意义，因为你们没有远见，没有真正的首领。

yingyinNormal.en: What makes a hundred dollar bill valuable, on the other hand, is how many or few of them are around.
yingyinNormal.zh: 而百元钞票的价值所在则是取决于它们数量的多寡。

yingyinNormal.en: What makes a hundred dollar bill valuable, on the other hand, is how many or few of them are around.
yingyinNormal.zh: 而百元钞票的价值所在则是取决于它们数量的多寡。

yingyinNormal.en: But what is it that makes that bill so much more interesting and valuable than other pieces of paper?
yingyinNormal.zh: 但是什么原因让这张钞票这么珍贵有趣，又和其他纸张不同呢？

yingyinNormal.en: But what is it that makes that bill so much more interesting and valuable than other pieces of paper?
yingyinNormal.zh: 但是什么原因让这张钞票这么珍贵有趣，又和其他纸张不同呢？

yingyinNormal.en: It doesn't seem to be discounted, it just seem to be something different, something valuable by itself.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那样就不是拿到折扣药品只不过是另一种不同的药品而已药物就可以体现自身价值。

yingyinNormal.en: That's a good point. My time is much too valuable. You know, perhaps I should find someone to do it for me.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这话说得对，我的时间太宝贵了，或许我该找个人帮我干这事。

examination_example.sentence: Helping forests flourish as <highlight>valuable</highlight> "carbon sinks" long into the future may require reducing their capacity to absorb carbon now.

examination_example.sentence_trans: 随着时间的推移，这些购买往往会变得更有价值。

word_usage.usage:
be valuable to sb.和be valuable for (doing) sth.都表示“对……有用”，如：
The book is valuable to me/for my purpose.
这本书对我很有用。

valuable，invaluable，precious都有“贵重的，有价值的”之意，区别在于：
valuable强调某物很值钱或对所有者具有极大的用途或利益；
invaluable多指不具体的事物，强调“极可贵的，无法估价的”；
precious指任何无法用钱衡量的珍贵的东西，尤其适用于失去后无法补偿的东西，还可用于人的感情方面。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 主要指值钱的，其次指有用的、有帮助的、有意义的。
侧重于事物本务的贵重，precious也侧重于人或事物在某人看来是可贵的。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2016.6-2023.6年8年间全四级试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight>考纲释义</highlight>
精选实考、考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2016-2023年51套试卷，包括阅读、听力、翻译等所有题型。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2016-2023年8年间试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

derivative_info_list.mean: adj. 贵重的；值钱的；非常重要的；非常有用的
v. 低估；看轻；对…估价过低

word_family.mean: n. 重要性；珍贵性；价值观念；标准；值；时值；确切意义；明暗度；价值

examination_example.sentence: While remote workers help to keep the café full in quiet times, they can take up the <highlight>valuable</highlight> table space in busy periods.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 虽然远程工作的人有助于保持咖啡馆在清闲时满座，但他们也会在忙碌时段占用宝贵的餐桌空间。

examination_example.sentence: If you believe you will live longer, then options become more <highlight>valuable</highlight>, and early commitment becomes less attractive.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 所以，如果你相信自己会活得更久，那么选择就变得更加重要，过早履行责任就变得不那么有吸引力了。

examination_example.sentence: That thing that you make is <highlight>valuable</highlight> to you and you can share it with others.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你创造的东西对你很有价值，你可以和别人分享。

sense_info_list.en: worth a great deal of money

examination_example.sentence: It shows how <highlight>valuable</highlight> an individual is.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它凸显了个人价值。

examination_example.sentence: His monstrous pearl was extremely <highlight>valuable</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他那颗巨大的珍珠极其珍贵。

examination_example.sentence: They just don't recognize it right now as particularly <highlight>valuable</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们只是现在不认为它特别有价值。
